definition: to see/to meet/to appear (to be sth)/to interview
variant of 人[ren2]/"person" radical in Chinese characters (Kangxi radical 10), occurring in 兒, 兀, 兄 etc
to meet with (sb who is paying a visit)/CL:次[ci4]
not to see/not to meet/to have disappeared/to be missing
it can clearly be seen (that this is the case)/it is (thus) clear/clear/visible
rare/not familiar (to the speaker)/sth rarely experience/hard to see
from this, it can be seen that...

sentences.english: No suspected cancer cells or cancer cells were found.
sentences.chinese: 宮頸刮片檢查兩組均未查見可疑癌細胞或癌細胞。

sentences.english: no one else can see you shake your head.
Back to the room to sleep, you may have seen her with the quilt, the mother.
sentences.chinese: 回房睡覺，也許你已見她加上的被子，那個是母親。

sentences.english: Can I see Mr. Matthews, please?
Today, I am within sight of my heaven.
sentences.chinese: 今天，我望得見我的天堂了。

sentences.english: He told his troubles to every Tom, Dick and Harry.
sentences.chinese: 他見人就訴說自己的煩惱，不論張三，抑或李四。

sentences.english: Don't give me any lip service. I want to see some action!
sentences.chinese: 別對我說好聽的，我要見你的行動。

sentences.english: Achilles is then told to go see Agamemnon.
sentences.chinese: 之後，阿喀琉斯被叫去見阿伽門農。

sentences.english: Since I hope to see you again, I'll say au revoir rather than adieu.
sentences.chinese: 因爲我希望再次見你，我將說再見，而非告別。

sentences.english: The village is no stranger to curious projects either.
sentences.chinese: 在華西村，各種奇奇怪怪的工程也不少見。

sentences.english: Sorry. Mr. Green can't see you now.
sentences.chinese: 對不起，格林師長教師此刻不能見您。

sentences.english: My English grandma saw my mum plant so many courgette and thought it was a bit strange.
sentences.chinese: 我奶奶見我媽種那麼多西葫蘆，覺得奇怪。

sentences.english: I think that in this life, I never see who can come to fish with the branches of Salix.
sentences.chinese: 我想，這輩子，我再也見不到誰能用柳樹枝來釣魚了。

sentences.english: The middle-aged man suddenly patted his head, Liu halal is hate see late.
sentences.chinese: 那中年人猛然拍拍腦袋，對劉清真是相恨見晚。
左撇子科學家其實並不少見。

sentences.english: I was hoping we could arrange to ③meet up either before or after.
sentences.chinese: 我希望，在那之前或之後我們能找個時間見一下。
